==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grapeshot
<hw>Grape"shot`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>
<def>A cluster, usually nine in number, of small iron balls, put
together by means of cast-iron circular plates at top and bottom, with
two rings, and a central connecting rod, in order to be used as a charge
for a cannon. Formerly grapeshot were inclosed in canvas bags.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grapestone</ent>⟦br⟧
